The Department of Water Affairs says while the province has received rain, it&#8217;s also experienced severe heat, which has countered the wet season. JOHANNESBURG The water affairs department is appealing for adherence to restrictions, warning the drought season has not yet passed.It says while the province has received rain it s also experienced severe heat, which has countered the wet season.Although there aren t any cuts looming, water use will dictate whether they will be introduced.The department says while it's noticed a slight rise in national dam levels, there s also been a decline in provincial levels in the past two weeks due to consumption.Spokesperson Sputnik Ratau says, If we are able to see water savings with time, we may not get to the possibility of water cuts. But where the savings are not coming, water restrictions may become one of the last options. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)